S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
J O I N T R E S O L U T I O N
MAKING AN APPROPRIATION OF $250,000 TO THE REFUGEE DREAM CENTER (RDC),
$250,000 TO HIGHER GROUND INTERNATIONAL, AND $250,000 TO DORCAS
INTERNATIONAL INSTITUTE OF RHODE ISLAND
Introduced By: Representatives Morales, Biah, Potter, Stewart, Batista, DeSimone,
Slater, Handy, Tanzi, and Furtado
Date Introduced: February 28, 2025
Referred To: House Finance
1 WHEREAS, The Refugee Dream Center (RDC), located in the City of Providence, is a
2 nonprofit 501(c)(3) founded by Dr. Omar Bah in 2015, with a primary focus on resettlement and
3 assistance with the challenges faced by refugees when they come to the United States; and
4 WHEREAS, The RDC “offers assistance in finding employment, education, and housing,
5 while also providing essential skills and knowledge such as navigating the U.S. healthcare
6 system, improving English language proficiency, and guiding individuals on the path to
7 citizenship”; and
8 WHEREAS, Higher Ground International and Dorcas International Institute of Rhode
9 Island are nonprofit organizations dedicated to assisting refugees and other marginalized
10 communities with refugee resettlement operations; and
11 WHEREAS, Under newly signed executive orders, the State Department’s refugee
12 program is now suspended and the RDC, Higher Ground International, and Dorcas International
13 Institute of Rhode Island have lost federal funding and staff; now, therefore be it
14 RESOLVED, That there is hereby appropriated, out of money in the treasury not
15 otherwise appropriated for the fiscal year 2025-2026, the sum of two hundred fifty thousand
16 dollars ($250,000) to the Refugee Dream Center (RDC), two hundred fifty thousand dollars
17 ($250,000) to Higher Ground International, and two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000) to
18 Dorcas International Institute of Rhode Island; and the state controller is hereby authorized and
19 directed to draw their orders upon the general treasurer for the payment of said sum, or so much

1 thereof as may be from time to time required, upon receipt of properly authenticated vouchers.
